---
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base.astro";

const meta = {
	description: "About Shameer Baramy. Backend, platform engineering, distributed systems, AI agents, and tools for thought.",
	title: "About",
};
---

<PageLayout meta={meta}>
	<section>
		<h1 class="heading-1">About</h1>
		<div class="prose">
			<p>
				I'm Shameer, a backend and platform engineer.
			</p>
			<p>
				Most of my work has been on backend services, distributed systems, and
				the internal platforms and tooling that engineering teams depend on. I
				write mostly Go and Python, with some TypeScript and Rust.
			</p>
			<p>
				The work I care about usually comes down to taking friction out of
				someone's day — the small, recurring things that slow people down. Most
				of it is unglamorous: a sharper tool, a shorter workflow, one fewer step
				between a person and what they were trying to do.
			</p>
			<p>
				On this site I write about platform engineering and developer
				productivity, LLM agents and the software you build around models,
				distributed systems and the ways they actually fail, and note-taking and
				tools for thought.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</PageLayout>
